== 与热可可的区别 ==
[[File:Drinking_Chocolate.webm|thumb]]
人们通常认为热巧克力和热可可是同一种饮品，但也有部分观点认为，热巧克力和热可可之间存在区别。<ref name="Nibble">{{cite web| last = The Nibble| title = Some Like It Hot: Hot Chocolate & Hot Cocoa Mixes: An Overview| publisher = Lifestyle Direct, Inc.| date = 2005–2008| url = http://www.thenibble.com/reviews/main/beverages/cocoas/hot-chocolate-overview.asp| accessdate = 2008-07-15| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20080917050557/http://www.thenibble.com/reviews/main/beverages/cocoas/hot-chocolate-overview.asp| archive-date = 2008-09-17| dead-url = yes}}</ref>热可可使用去除[[可可脂|可可脂]]的磨制可可豆制成，而热巧克力可直接由巧克力棒制成，巧克力棒中则包含可可、糖以及可可脂。两者的主要区别在于可可脂。<ref name="Rediscover" /><ref name="Term">{{cite web|url=http://www.statssheet.com/articles/article61849.html|title=Why Hot Cocoa Is Healthier Than Hot Chocolate|last=Craddock|first=Darren|accessdate=2008-06-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090122111445/http://www.statssheet.com/articles/article61849.html|archive-date=2009-01-22|dead-url=yes}}</ref>去除可可脂的热可可脂肪含量显著比热巧克力低，同时仍保留巧克力中所有的[[抗氧化剂|抗氧化剂]]。<ref name="daily">{{cite web|url=https://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2003/11/031106051159.htm|title=Hot Cocoa Tops Red Wine And Tea In Antioxidants; May Be Healthier Choice|website=Science Daily|date=2003-11-06|accessdate=2008-06-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080702022232/http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2003/11/031106051159.htm|archive-date=2008-07-02|dead-url=no}}</ref>

制作热巧克力可以将黑巧克力或牛奶巧克力切成小块加入牛奶中，并添加食糖。而美式即食热可可粉通常包含奶粉等原料，所以无需添加牛奶亦可制作。<ref name="Nibble"/>在英国，“热巧克力”是一种甜的巧克力饮料，液体为热牛奶或水，而粉末为巧克力、糖和奶粉。“可可”则是一种类似的饮料，但仅包含热牛奶和可可粉，可以添加食糖增甜，也可不添加糖直接饮用。<ref name="Nibble"/>
{{clear}}

== 各地制作方法 ==
今天，人们认为热巧克力、热可可等饮料是[[疗癒美食|疗癒美食]]，世界各地皆饮用这些饮料。欧洲的热巧克力相对更浓郁，而美国的速食热巧克力则较稀。热巧克力不是一种[[茶|茶]]，但[[尼日利亚|尼日利亚]]人认为早晨饮用的饮料都是“茶”，因此将热巧克力归为“茶”。<ref>{{cite web|author=Kperogi, Farooq|url=http://web.archive.org/web/20170223030623/http://www.dailytrust.com.ng/sunday/index.php/politics-of-grammar/15779-qa|title=Q and A on the grammar of food, usage and Nigerian English|publisher=''{{tsl|en|Media Trust|Daily Trust}}''|date=2014-01-26|accessdate=2017-02-23|quote=We call everything we drink in the morning "tea" even if it’s not.[...]"Daddy, why do Nigerians call hot cocoa ‘tea’?" she asked me.|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170223030623/http://www.dailytrust.com.ng/sunday/index.php/politics-of-grammar/15779-qa|archive-date=2017-02-23|dead-url=yes}}</ref>许多地区皆有独特的配料，例如棉花糖、奶油和芝士。<ref name="Thicker" /><ref name="European" /><ref name="Nikkitha Bakshani" />

=== 欧洲 ===
[[File:chocolademelk.jpg|thumb]]
[[File:Chocolate_with_churros.jpg|thumb]]。|alt=画面右侧是一杯浓稠、微微冒泡的热巧克力，一个不锈钢勺子插入巧克力中，杯子放置在杯垫上，杯身写着“ITAL CAFFÈ”。左侧是一盘六根交叠、弯曲的西班牙油条，每根呈长条状，表面有顺着长边的凹槽。]]

在欧洲大陆，尤其是西班牙和意大利，由于使用了[[玉米淀粉|-{zh-cn:玉米淀粉;zh-tw:玉米澱粉;zh-hk:粟米澱粉;}-]]等增稠的材料，热巧克力通常十分浓厚。<ref name="European">{{cite web|last1=McGavin|first1=Jennifer|title=Kakao oder Heisse Schokolade|url=https://www.thespruce.com/kakao-oder-heisse-schokolade-1446917|publisher=the spruce|accessdate=2017-07-09|date=2017-04-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170930090912/https://www.thespruce.com/kakao-oder-heisse-schokolade-1446917|archive-date=2017-09-30|dead-url=no}}</ref>意大利的“cioccolata calda”便是欧洲一种粘稠的热巧克力。<ref>{{cite book|author={{tsl|en|Eric Lanlard|Eric Lanlard}}|title=Totally Chocolate: 60 deliciously seductive recipes|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=qFFOBAAAQBAJ|year=2014|publisher={{tsl|en|Mitchell Beazley|Mitchell Beazley}}|page=170|access-date=2018-08-01|archive-date=2021-09-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210909005326/https://books.google.com/books?id=qFFOBAAAQBAJ|dead-url=no}}</ref>在西班牙，熱巧克力和[[西班牙油条|西班牙油条]]是工人的傳統[[早餐|早餐]]。這種西班牙式的熱巧克力很濃，有[[布丁|布丁]]的黏稠度。<ref name="NatGeo">{{cite web|last1=Hall|first1=Christopher|title=Where to Find the Best Hot Chocolate and Churros in Spain|url=http://travel.nationalgeographic.com/travel/international-foods/hot-chocolate-churros-spain/|work=National Geographic Traveler|accessdate=2020-06-29|date=2010-01-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170327105649/http://travel.nationalgeographic.com/travel/international-foods/hot-chocolate-churros-spain|archive-date=2017-03-27|dead-url=no}}</ref>

热巧克力在荷兰也是十分流行的饮料，其名为“warme chocolademelk”，人们通常在家中或咖啡店中饮用热巧克力。法国的热巧克力常常在早餐时间供应，有时巧克力中会浸入涂抹了黄油、果酱、蜂蜜或[[能多益|能多益]]的面包条。<ref>{{cite web|last1=Poncelin|first1=Pamela|title=Culinary Ambassadors: Breakfast in France|url=http://www.seriouseats.com/2010/09/culinary-ambassadors-breakfast-in-france.html|publisher=Serious Eats|accessdate=2017-07-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170709021811/http://www.seriouseats.com/2010/09/culinary-ambassadors-breakfast-in-france.html|archive-date=2017-07-09|dead-url=no}}</ref>

在德国，使用融化的巧克力制作的热巧克力（{{lang|de|Heiße Schokolade Wiener Art}}）与使用粉末制作的热巧克力（{{lang|de|Trinkschokolade}}）是不同的。<ref name="European" />热巧克力上常铺有奶油。<ref name="European" />

欧洲还存在更多热巧克力的变种。若客人于比利时的咖啡馆中点一杯“{{lang|nl|warme chocolade}}”或“{{lang|fr|chocolat chaud}}”，热牛奶和苦巧克力片将分别呈上，由客人自行调配。<ref name="Nibble" />[[维也纳|维也纳]]式变种“{{lang|de|Heiße Schokolade Wiener Art}}”则使用蛋黄增稠。<ref name="European" />

=== 北美洲 ===
[[File:Hot_chocolate.jpg|thumb]]。|alt=一杯热巧克力，奶油近乎要满出杯口，奶油上撒有可可粉，放有一颗棉花糖。杯子右侧有一个圆形把手，放置于杯垫上。]]
美国和加拿大流行的热巧克力制作简单，将包含可可粉、糖、奶粉的混合粉末加入热水或牛奶中即可。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/3883796/|title=Hot chocolate like you've never tasted before|last=Rosengarten|first=David|date=2004-01-06|publisher=TODAY|accessdate=2009-12-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20040806184941/http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/3883796/|archive-date=2004-08-06|dead-url=no}}</ref>这种热巧克力的变种较稀且甜，可搭配[[棉花糖_(颗粒状)|棉花糖]]、[[鲜奶油|奶油]]或一块固态巧克力。<ref name="Thicker">{{cite news|url=https://www.usatoday.com/printedition/life/20061208/dd_chocolate08.art.htm|title=Warming up to real hot chocolate |last=Billet|first=Felisa|date=2009-10-23|work=USA TODAY|accessdate=2009-12-20}}</ref>17世纪，荷兰人将热巧克力带到北美洲，但1775年起殖民者才开始销售热巧克力。<ref name="Illustrated">{{Cite book|last=Morton|first=Marcia|author2=Frederic Morton|title=Chocolate, an Illustrated History|url=https://archive.org/details/chocolateillustr0000mort|publisher=Crown Publishers|location=New York|year=1986}}</ref>传统上，美国人喜欢在寒冷的冬天饮用热巧克力。<ref name="guardian history trend" />

热巧克力与[[浓缩咖啡|浓缩咖啡]]或[[咖啡|咖啡]]调配而成的饮料在美国也受到欢迎，称作[[摩卡咖啡|摩卡咖啡]]。这一名称源自[[也门|也门]]小镇[[摩卡|摩卡]]，该地种植着一种名为“摩卡”的咖啡。<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.differencebetween.net/object/comparisons-of-food-items/difference-between-mocha-and-coffee/|title=Difference Between Mocha and Coffee {{!}} Difference Between {{!}} Mocha vs Coffee|author=Emelda M.|date=2012-01-11|website=DifferenceBetween.net|language=en|access-date=2020-06-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200509015018/http://www.differencebetween.net/object/comparisons-of-food-items/difference-between-mocha-and-coffee/|archive-date=2020-05-09|dead-url=no}}</ref>此外，添加了香料的传统热巧克力也重新在美国出现，受到巧克力品鉴家的欢迎。<ref name="guardian history trend" />

热巧克力还是墨西哥流行的国民饮料，其包含牛奶巧克力、[[肉桂|肉桂]]、糖以及[[香荚兰|香荚兰]]。<ref name="Moncayo">{{cite web|last1=Moncayo|first1=Jennifer|title=Mexican Chocolate: A Short History & Recipe|url=http://thelatinkitchen.com/how/ingredients/a/mexican-chocolate-short-history-recipe|publisher=The Latin Kitchen|accessdate=2017-07-15|date=2013-01-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170821074508/http://thelatinkitchen.com/how/ingredients/a/mexican-chocolate-short-history-recipe|archive-date=2017-08-21|dead-url=no}}</ref>这种热巧克力一般以圆形或六边形片剂售卖，能溶于热牛奶、水或奶油，混合后会产生一层-{奶油色}-的泡沫。<ref name="Moncayo" />1942年，一篇《[[芝加哥论坛报|芝加哥论坛报]]》的文章描述道，饮用墨西哥肉桂热巧克力时常常搭配各式墨西哥甜味油酥糕点，如{{tsl|en|Pan dulce|甜面包}}和西班牙油条。<ref>{{cite news|last1=Johnson|first1=Dorothy|title=Hot Chocolate is Historical Mexican Drink|url=https://www.newspapers.com/newspage/370741717/|page=83|accessdate=2020-06-29|publisher=Chicago Tribune|date=1942-12-06|subscription=yes|archive-date=2021-09-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210909005421/https://www.newspapers.com/newspage/370741717/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== 南美洲 ===
哥伦比亚的热巧克力使用特质容器{{tsl|en|Chocolatera|chocolatera}}来盛装，并用木质搅拌棒{{tsl|en|Molinillo (whisk)|molinillo}}来制作。哥伦比亚人通常在早餐时享用热巧克力，并搭配面包以及新鲜柔软的农场芝士。<ref name="Nikkitha Bakshani">{{cite web|last1=Bakshani|first1=Nikkitha|title=Colombian Hot Chocolate: Just Add Cheese|url=https://www.thedailymeal.com/travel/columbian-hot-chocolate-just-add-cheese|publisher=The Daily Meal|accessdate=2017-07-09|date=2015-03-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170628082806/https://www.thedailymeal.com/travel/columbian-hot-chocolate-just-add-cheese|archive-date=2017-06-28|dead-url=no}}</ref>类似地，[[厄瓜多尔|厄瓜多尔]]的热巧克力也同样在饮料顶端放有芝士。<ref name="latin">{{cite web|title=Hot Chocolate in Latin America|url=http://www.vivatravelguides.com/live-list/latin/hot-chocolate-in-latin-america/|publisher=Viva Travel Guides|accessdate=2017-07-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170930170445/http://www.vivatravelguides.com/live-list/latin/hot-chocolate-in-latin-america/|archive-date=2017-09-30|dead-url=no}}</ref>

在[[秘鲁|秘鲁]]，[[圣诞节|圣诞节]]时南半球的夏季已经开始，但人们依然会在早餐时间饮用热巧克力，同时食用[[意大利面包|意大利-{zh-cn:面包;zh-tw:麵包;zh-hk:麪包;}-]]。<ref>{{cite web|title=The curious Peruvian tradition of drinking hot chocolate and paneton in summer|url=https://rischmoller.wordpress.com/2012/11/30/the-curious-peruvian-tradition-of-drinking-hot-chocolate-and-paneton-in-summer/|publisher=Rischmoller Real Estate|accessdate=2017-07-09|date=2012-11-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170930131152/https://rischmoller.wordpress.com/2012/11/30/the-curious-peruvian-tradition-of-drinking-hot-chocolate-and-paneton-in-summer/|archive-date=2017-09-30|dead-url=no}}</ref>另外，许多秘鲁人会将巧克力酱加入饮料中。<ref name="latin" />[[阿根廷|阿根廷]]的“{{lang|es|submarino}}”也是一种巧克力饮料，将巧克力棒和糖加入沸腾的牛奶中制成。<ref name="latin" />

=== 亚洲 ===
[[File:Dumaguete_Sta_Monica_Beach_Club_-_Suman_Mangga_Tsokolate_2.jpg|thumb]]的巧克力饮料“{{tsl|en|tsokolate|tsokolate}}”，搭配椰汁糯米甜品{{tsl|en|suman (food)|苏曼 (食物)|苏曼}}和{{tsl|en|Carabao (mango)|吕宋芒}}。|alt=画面左上角是一杯巧克力，杯口两侧较低。左下角是半个吕宋芒，切成小块，并翻成拱形。右侧是长条形、用叶子包裹的糯米甜品苏曼。]]
[[菲律宾|菲律宾]]当地的巧克力饮料称作“{{tsl|en|tsokolate|tsokolate}}”，由研磨烤可可豆制成的巧克力片“tabliya”（又称“tablea”）冲泡水或牛奶而成。<ref name="FLR tablet vocabulary">{{cite journal|title=菲律宾英语:语言迁移及其深层机理探究|author1=袁友芹|author2=张敬爽|journal=外语学刊|year=2010|volume=6|pages=73-75|doi=10.16263/j.cnki.23-1071/h.2010.06.036}}</ref>与南美洲和西班牙版本类似，都是用{{tsl|en|Chocolatera|chocolatera}}以及{{tsl|en|Molinillo (whisk)|molinillo}}来制作，因此泡沫较多。Tsokolate通常会放[[黑糖|黑糖]]，有一种独特的粗糙口感。<ref name="polistico">{{cite book|author =Polistico, Edgie|title =Philippine Food, Cooking, & Dining Dictionary|publisher =Anvil Publishing, Incorporated|year =2017|isbn =9786214200870|url =https://books.google.com/books?id=STSWDwAAQBAJ&pg=PT813|access-date =2020-06-23|archive-date =2021-09-09|archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20210909011237/https://books.google.com/books?id=STSWDwAAQBAJ&pg=PT813|dead-url =no}}</ref><ref name="cabrera">{{cite web |last1=Cabrera |first1=Maryanne |title=sokolate (Filipino Hot Chocolate) |url=https://www.thelittleepicurean.com/2018/01/tsokolate-filipino-hot-chocolate.html |website=The Little Epicurean |accessdate=2018-12-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181214213832/https://www.thelittleepicurean.com/2018/01/tsokolate-filipino-hot-chocolate.html |archive-date=2018-12-14 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

Tsokolate在[[邦板牙语|邦板牙语]]中称作“suklati”、{{tsl|en|Maguindanao language|马京达瑙语}}中称作“sikulate”、[[米沙鄢语支|米沙鄢语支]]中称作“sikwate”或“sikuwate”，都源自西班牙语词汇“chocolate”。<ref name="polistico"/>

Tsokolate通常搭配菲律宾传统米糕“{{tsl|en|kakanin|kakanin}}”或面包“{{tsl|en|pandesal|pandesal}}”饮用。{{tsl|en|Christmas in the Philippines|菲律宾圣诞节|圣诞节}}时最受欢迎。<ref name="cabrera"/>
